  "title": "Pilgrim's Progress §145: APOL.",
  "body": "APOL. Thou hast done in this, according to the proverb, \"Changed a bad for a worse\"; but it is ordinary for those that have professed themselves his servants, after a while to give him the slip, and return again to me. Do thou so too, and all shall be well. CHR. I have given him my faith, and sworn my allegiance to him; how, then, can I go back from this, and not be hanged as a traitor? APOL. Thou didst the same to me, and yet I am willing to pass by all, if now thou wilt yet turn again and go back.",
